{"questionId":"9069434","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Carbon forms many compounds.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>But-2-ene reacts with hydrogen bromide.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write the equation for the reaction between but-2-ene and hydrogen bromide.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>CH<sub>3</sub>CH=CHCH<sub>3</sub> (g) + HBr (g) → CH<sub>3</sub>CH<sub>2</sub>CHBrCH<sub>3</sub> (l)</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p>C<sub>4</sub>H<sub>8</sub> (g) + HBr (g) → C<sub>4</sub>H<sub>9</sub>Br (l) ✔</p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069434","referenceCode":"22M.2.sl.TZ2.4d(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Write the equation for the reaction between but-2-ene and hydrogen bromide.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.2 Functional group chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}